{"name": "chide", "metadata": {"name": "chide", "version": "3.0.1", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 5 - Production/Stable", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/cjw296/chide", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Quickly create sample objects from data.", "upload_time": 1733389963}, "documentation": ["---\nsubstitutions:\n  CircleCI: |-\n    ```{image} https://circleci.com/gh/cjw296/chide/tree/master.svg?style=shield\n    ```\n  Docs: |-\n    ```{image} https://readthedocs.org/projects/chide/badge/?version=latest\n    ```\n---\n\n# Chide\n\n[CircleCI] [Docs]\n\nQuickly create and compare sample objects.\n\nChide's philosophy is to give you a simple registry of parameters\nneeded to instantiate objects for your tests.\nThere's also support for simplifying objects down to mappings of their attributes\nfor easier comparison and rendering, along with parsing and rendering of formats\nfor inserting or asserting about multiple objects that are naturally tabular.\n\n## Quickstart\n\nSay we have two classes that each require two parameters in order to\nbe instantiated:\n\n```python\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\n\n@dataclass\nclass ClassOne:\n  x: int\n  y: int\n\n@dataclass\nclass ClassTwo:\n  a: int\n  b: ClassOne\n```\n\nWe can set up a registry of sample values as follows:\n\n```python\nfrom chide import Collection\n\nsamples = Collection({\n    ClassOne: {'x': 1, 'y': 2},\n    ClassTwo: {'a': 1, 'b': ClassOne},\n})\n```\n\nNow we can quickly make sample objects:\n\n```pycon\n>>> samples.make(ClassOne)\nClassOne(x=1, y=2)\n```\n\nWe can provide our own overrides if we want:\n\n```pycon\n>>> samples.make(ClassOne, y=3)\nClassOne(x=1, y=3)\n```\n\nWe can also create nested trees of objects:\n\n```pycon\n>>> samples.make(ClassTwo)\nClassTwo(a=1, b=ClassOne(x=1, y=2))\n```\n\n[circleci]: https://circleci.com/gh/cjw296/tree/chide\n[docs]: http://chide.readthedocs.org/en/latest/\n"], "modules": [{"name": "chide.typing", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "chide.typing.Attrs", "type": {"name": "TypeAlias", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.TypeAlias", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "chide.typing.Identifier", "type": {"name": "TypeAlias", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.TypeAlias", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "chide.set", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "chide.set.T", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "chide.set.Set", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "chide.set.Set.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "collection", "type": {"name": "Collection", "xref": {"fqname": "chide.Collection", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "identify", "type": {"name": "Identifier | None", "xref": null, "params": null}, "default": "..."}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "chide.set.Set.get", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "type_", "type": {"name": "Type", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Type", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "T", "xref": {"fqname": "T", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "**attrs", "type": {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "T", "xref": {"fqname": "T", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Return an appropriate sample object of the specified `type_`.\n\nThe `attrs` mapping will be overlaid onto the sample attributes\nfound in this set's {class}`~chide.Collection` before checking if\nan appropriate sample object already exists in the set.\n\nIf one exists, it is returned. If not, one is created using\nthis set's {class}`~chide.Collection`, added to the set and then\nreturned.\n"]}], "class_variables": [{"name": "chide.set.Set.identify", "type": {"name": "Identifier", "xref": {"fqname": "chide.set.typing.Identifier", "project": null}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["A collection of sample objects where only one object with\na given identity may exist at one time.\n\n```\nparam collection\n\nThe  instance used to create sample objects\nwhen necessary.\n\nparam identify\n\nAn  callable that takes\n and  parameters.\n\n, usually a class, is the type of the\nsample object being requested.\n\n is a  of the attributes being requested for the\nsample object to have.\n\nThe callable should return a hashable value that indicates the identity\nto use for the requested sample object. For each unique hashable value,\nonly one sample object will be instantiated and returned each time\na sample is requested where this callable returns the given identity.\n\nNone may be returned to indicate that a new object should always\nbe returned for the provided parameters.\n```\n"]}], "exports": []}, {"name": "chide.factory", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "chide.factory.T", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "chide.factory.Factory", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "chide.factory.Factory.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "collection", "type": {"name": "Collection", "xref": {"fqname": "chide.factory.collection.Collection", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "type_", "type": {"name": "Type", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Type", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "T", "xref": {"fqname": "T", "project": null}, "params": null}]}, "default": null}, {"name": "attrs", "type": {"